%N A096823 Numbers of the form p*(p+(2n-1))/2 created with smallest primes of form p=2^x-(2n-1)=A096522(n). Here the exponent equals x=A096502[n], the least exponent providing this kind of primes. Peculiarity of the present terms is as follows: Mod[sigma[a(n)],a[n]]=2*n.
%C A096823 These numbers are clearly analogous to perfect numbers.
